ccessful effort to mobilize the media and public opinion overwhelmed the business community and organized labor and persuaded Javits's colleagues in Congress to support comprehensive pension reform legislation. The enactment of ERISA in September 1974 recast federal policy for private pension plans by making worker security an overriding objective of federal law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aPension trustsxHistoryxUnited States. 0aPension trustsxLaw and legislationxHistoryxUnited States. 0aPension trustsxLaw and legislationzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aPension trustszUnited StatesxHistory. 7aMEDICAL / Health Policy.2bisacsh  abusiness economics.  acapitalism.  acongress.  aemployee benefits.  aemployee retirement income security act.  aerisa.  afederal law.  afinance.  afree markets.  agovernment policy.  agovernment regulation.  ahealth plans.  ahealth policy.  ahistory.  ainsurance.  ajacob k javits.  ajavits.  alabor unions.  alabor.  alegislation.  amarxism.  anonfiction.  apension reform.  apensions.  apersonal finance.  apolitical history.  apolitics.  aprivate pension plans.  aretirement plans.  aretirement.  aunions.  aworker security.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093139840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520931398423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520931398/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles